OT Evan Neal Alabama 86
info: Evan Neal is another monster coming out of the powerhouse high school IMG and committing to the college powerhouse Alabama. He was a 5 star recruit at 6’7 370 whcih dwarfs everyone standing near him. He immediately stepped in and started at left guard alongside Leatherwood to help Alabama dominate another season and was named a freshman all american. He then moved to right tackle during his second season where he won a national championship.
pros: Monster of a build. Moves people in the run game. Long arm, can get on defenders easily. Very easy mover especially for the size. Improved as the 2020 season progressed. Great patience in his pass sets
cons: Stops feet on contact in pass sets allowing defenders to run around. Although good length, defenders can get into his chest to easy. Didn’t pick up stunts very well. Played off balance too often.
takeaway: Neal has all the size and athleticism to be a great NFL tackle. He has started from day one and has shown a lot of promise to be a great lineman. Although Neal may take a few years to fully develop his ceiling is very high.
